annotationA: Delta-1-Pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase 1 is a conserved, nuclear-encoded mitochondrial matrix enzyme. It is a member of the aldehyde dehydrogenase superfamily involved in proline degradation
annotationB: Glutamate oxaloacetate transaminase 1, isoform B; L-aspartate:2-oxoglutarate aminotransferase activity; pyridoxal phosphate binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: aspartate metabolic process; imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis; glutamate biosynthetic process
